main event: On 23 June 1966, a UFO sighting was reported in Columbus, Mississippi, which was observed visually and tracked by radar.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 21 minutes visually and 4 minutes on radar., The object was reported to be stationary during the observation., There was no physical evidence available to evaluate the sighting., Additional information was requested from the witness but was never received., The conclusion stated insufficient data for proper evaluation.
